ProScriptFunction.Description: Get Year from TrialMaster date
ProScriptFunction.Body: DECLARE @retVal nvarchar(4) BEGIN WITH tokens(p, a, b) AS ( SELECT 1, 1, charindex('/', @DataValue) UNION ALL SELECT p + 1, b + 1, charindex('/', @DataValue, b + 1) FROM tokens WHERE b > 0 ) SELECT @retVal = LTRIM(RTRIM(substring(@DataValue, a, CASE WHEN b > 0 THEN b-a ELSE 4000 END))) FROM tokens WHERE p = 1 END IF LEN(@retVal) = 4 AND ISNUMERIC(@retVal) = 1 RETURN @retVal RETURN null

nvarchar(10)) -- populate whe stop words are populated at the time of function generation INSERT INTO @StopWords(stopWord) VALUES ('UNK'),('NA') -- make sure there are two / characters in the date WHILE (LEN(@date)-LEN(REPLACE(@date,'/','')) < 2) SET @date = @date + '/' -- populate @DateAndTimeParts with date and time parts DECLARE @DXML AS XML = CAST(('' + REPLACE(@date, '/', '') + '') AS XML) INSERT INTO @DateAndTimeParts (IsStopWord, FixedValue) SELECT CASE WHEN N.value('.', 'VARCHAR(10)')='' THEN 1 WHEN s.stopWord IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE 1 END, ISNULL(NULLIF(N.value('.', 'VARCHAR(10)'),''),(SELECT TOP 1 stopWord FROM @StopWords)) FROM @DXML.nodes('i') as T(N) LEFT OUTER JOIN @StopWords s ON s.stopWord = N.value('.', 'VARCHAR(10)') -- validate date parts: Replace (LEN(FixedValue) != 2 OR ISNUMERIC(FixedValue) != 1 OR FixedValue not between 1 and 12) THEN '-' --month WHEN (id = 3) AND (LEN(FixedValue) != 2 OR ISNUMERIC(FixedValue) != 1 OR FixedValue not between 1 and 31) THEN '-' --day ELSE FixedValue END -- the date is invalid in case one part is empty('-') and it's not a stop word IF(EXISTS(SELECT 1 FROM @DateAndTimeParts WHERE FixedValue = '-' AND IsStopWord = 0)) GOTO INVALID_DATE -- delete trailing empty ('-') date and time values from @dateParts WHILE EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM @DateAndTimeParts WHERE FixedValue = '-' AND id = (select max(id) from @DateAndTimeParts)) DELETE FROM @DateAndTimeParts WHERE FixedValue = '-' AND id = (select max(id) from @DateAndTimeParts) -- get day component SELECT @year = NULLIF(FixedValue,'-') FROM @DateAndTimeParts WHERE id = 1 SELECT @month = NULLIF(FixedValue,'-') FROM @DateAndTimeParts WHERE id = 2 SELECT @day = NULLIF(FixedValue,'-') FROM @DateAndTimeParts WHERE id = 3 -- validate day ProSDTMVariable.Caption: STUDYID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique identifier for a study.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOMAIN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: USUBJID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESEQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEGRPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a subject.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEREFID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Internal or external identifier such as a serial number on an SAE reporting form

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined identifier. It may be pre-printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor‘s operational database. Example: Line number on an Adverse Events page.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AETERM
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Reported Term for the Adverse Event
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Verbatim name of the event.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEMODIFY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: If AETERM is modified to facilitate coding, then AEMODIFY will contain the modified text.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEDECOD
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Dictionary-derived text description of AETERM or AEMODIFY. Equivalent to the Preferred Term (PT in MedDRA). The sponsor is expected to provide the dictionary name and version used to map the terms utilizing the define.xml external codelist attributes

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AECAT
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to define a Category of related records. Example: BLEEDING, NEUROPSYCHIATRIC.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: A further Categorization of adverse event. Example: NEUROLOGIC.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEPRESP
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: A value of "Y" indicates that this adverse event was pre-specified on the CRF. Values are null for spontaneously reported events (i.e., those collected as free-text verbatim terms)

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEBODSYS
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Dictionary derived. Body system or organ class used by the sponsor from the coding dictionary (e.g., MedDRA). When using a multi-axial dictionary such as MedDRA, this should contain the SOC used for the sponsor‘s analyses and summary tables which may not necessarily be the primary SOC.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AELOC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes anatomical location relevant for the event (e.g., LEFT ARM for skin rash).

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESEV
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: The severity or intensity of the event. Examples: MILD, MODERATE, SEVERE.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESER
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Is this a serious event?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEACN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes changes to the study treatment as a result of the event. AEACN is specifically for the relationship to study treatment. AEACNOTH is for actions unrelated to dose adjustments of study treatment. Examples of AEACN values include ICH E2B values: DRUG WITHDRAWN, DOSE REDUCED, DOSE INCREASED, DOSE NOT CHANGED, UNKNOWN or NOT APPLICABLE

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEACNOTH
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes other actions taken as a result of the event that are unrelated to dose adjustments of study treatment. Usually reported as free text. Example: "TREATMENT UNBLINDED. PRIMARY CARE PHYSICIAN NOTIFIED."

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEREL
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Records the investigator's opinion as to the causality of the event to the treatment. ICH E2A and E2B examples include NOT RELATED, UNLIKELY RELATED, POSSIBLY RELATED, RELATED. Controlled Terminology may be defined in the future. Check with regulatory authority for population of this variable

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AERELNST
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Records the investigator's opinion as to whether the event may have been due to a treatment other than study drug. May be reported as free text. Example: "MORE LIKELY RELATED TO ASPIRIN USE.".

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEPATT
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to indicate the pattern of the event over time. Examples: INTERMITTENT, CONTINUOUS, SINGLE EVENT.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEOUT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Description of the outcome of an event.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESCAN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Was the serious event associated with the development of cancer?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESCONG
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Was the serious event associated with congenital anomaly or birth defect?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESDISAB
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Did the serious event result in persistent or significant disability/incapacity?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESDTH
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Did the serious event result in death?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESHOSP
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Did the serious event require or prolong hospitalization?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESLIFE
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Was the serious event life threatening?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESOD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Did the serious event occur with an overdose?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESMIE
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Do additional categories for seriousness apply?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AECONTRT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Was another treatment given because of the occurrence of the event?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AETOXGR
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Toxicity grade according to a standard toxicity scale such as Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events v3.0 (CTCAE). Sponsor should specify name of the scale and version used in the metadata (see 6.2.1.1, Assumption 6c). If value is from a numeric scale, represent only the number (e.g., "2" and not "Grade 2").

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESTDY
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Study Day of Start of Adverse Event
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Study day of start of adverse event relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEENDY
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Study Day of End of Adverse Event
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Study day of end of event relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEDUR
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Collected duration and unit of an adverse event. Used only if collected on the CRF and not derived from start and end date/times. Example: P1DT2H (for 1 day, 2 hours).

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEENRF
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes the end of the event relative to the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point (RFSTDTC) and a discrete ending point (RFENDTC) of the trial.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEENRTPT
ProSDTMVariable.Description: End Relative to Reference Time Point
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifies the end of the event as being before or after the reference time point defined by variable AEENTPT.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEENTPT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Description of date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the reference point referred to by AEENRTPT. Examples: "2003-12-25" or "VISIT 2".

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: STUDYID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique identifier for a study.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOMAIN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: USUBJID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CESEQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CEGRPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to tie together a block of related records for a subject within a domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CEREFID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Internal or external identifier.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CESPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined reference number. Perhaps pre-printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor‘s operational database. Example: Line number on a CRF page.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CETERM
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Reported Term for the Clinical Event
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Term for the medical condition or event. Most likely pre-printed on CRF.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CEDECOD
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Controlled terminology for the name of the clinical event. The sponsor is expected to provide the dictionary name and version used to map the terms utilizing the define.xml external codelist attributes

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CECAT
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to define a Category of related records.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CESCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: A further Categorization of the condition or event.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CEPRESP
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to indicate whether the Event in CETERM was pre-specified. Value is Y for pre-specified events, null for spontaneously reported events.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CEOCCUR
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used when the occurrence of specific events is solicited to indicate whether or not a clinical event occurred. Values are null for spontaneously reported events.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CESTAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: The status indicates that a question from a pre-specified list was not answered.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CEREASND
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes the reason clinical event data was not collected. Used in conjunction with CESTAT when value is NOT DONE.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CEBODSYS
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Dictionary-derived. Body system or organ class that is involved in an event or measurement from a standard hierarchy (e.g., MedDRA). When using a multi-axial dictionary such as MedDRA, this should contain the SOC used for the sponsor‘s analyses and summary tables which may not necessarily be the primary SOC.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CESEV
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: The severity or intensity of the event. Examples: MILD, MODERATE, SEVERE

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CEDY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Study day of clinical event collection, measured as integer days. 2. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics. This formula should be consistent across the submission.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CESTRF
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes the start of the clinical event relative to the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point (represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics).

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CEENRF
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes the end of the event relative to the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point (represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics).

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CESTRTPT
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Start Relative to Reference Time Point
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifies the start of the observation as being before or after the reference time point defined by variable CESTTPT.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CESTTPT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the sponsor-defined reference point referred to by --STRTPT. Examples: "2003-12-15" or "VISIT 1".

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CEENRTPT
ProSDTMVariable.Description: End Relative to Reference Time Point
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifies the end of the event as being before or after the reference time point defined by variable CEENTPT.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CEENTPT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the reference point referred to by CEENRTPT. Examples: "2003-12-25" or "VISIT 2".

ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique identifier for a study.

ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DSGRPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a subject.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DSREFID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Internal or external identifier.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DSSPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined reference number. Perhaps pre-printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor‘s operational database. Example: Line number on a Disposition page.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DSTERM
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Reported Term for the Disposition Event
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Verbatim name of the event or protocol milestone. Some terms in DSTERM will match DSDECOD, but others, such as "Subject moved" will map to controlled terminology in DSDECOD, such as "LOST TO FOLLOW-UP."

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DSDECOD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Controlled terminology for the name of disposition event or protocol milestone. Examples of protocol milestones: INFORMED CONSENT OBTAINED, RANDOMIZED

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DSCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to define a Category of related records. DSCAT is now an "Expected" variable. DSCAT was permissible in SDTMIG 3.1.1 and earlier versions. The change from "permissible" to "expected" is based on the requirement to distinguish protocol milestones and/or other events from disposition events. DSCAT may be null if there are only "disposition events"; however, it is recommended that DSCAT always be populated.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DSSCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: A further Categorization of disposition event.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EPOCH
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: EPOCH may be used when DSCAT = "DISPOSITION EVENT". Examples: SCREENING, TREATMENT PHASE, FOLLOW-UP

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DSSTDY
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Study Day of Start of Disposition Event
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Study day of start of event relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DVREFID

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DVSPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined reference number. Perhaps pre-printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor‘s operational database. Example: Line number on a CRF page.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DVTERM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Verbatim name of the protocol deviation criterion. Example: IVRS PROCESS DEVIATION - NO DOSE CALL PERFORMED. The DVTERM values will map to the controlled terminology in DVDECOD, such as TREATMENT DEVIATION.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DVDECOD

ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Controlled terminology for the name of the protocol deviation. Examples: SUBJECT NOT WITHDRAWN AS PER PROTOCOL, SELECTION CRITERIA NOT MET, EXCLUDED CONCOMITANT MEDICATION, TREATMENT DEVIATION.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DVCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Category of the protocol deviation criterion.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DVSCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: A further Categorization of the protocol deviation.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EPOCH
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Epoch associated with the start date/time of the deviation. Examples: TREATMENT PHASE, SCREENING, and FOLLOW-UP.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DVSTDTC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Start date/time of deviation represented in ISO 8601 character format.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DVENDTC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: End date/time of deviation represented in ISO 8601 character format.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESPID

ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Dictionary-derived text description of the Lowest Level Term.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AELLTCD

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEPTCD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Dictionary-derived code for the Preferred Term.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEHLT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Dictionary-derived text description of the High Level Term for the primary System Organ Class.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEHLTCD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Dictionary-derived code for the High Level Term for the primary System Organ Class.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEHLGT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Dictionary-derived text description of the High Level Group Term for the primary System Organ Class.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEHLGTCD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Dictionary-derived code for the High Level Group Term for the primary System Organ Class.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AECAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to define a category of related records. Example: BLEEDING, NEUROPSYCHIATRIC.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: A further categorization of adverse event. Example: NEUROLOGIC.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEPRESP
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: A value of Y indicates that this adverse event was pre-specified on the CRF. Values are null for spontaneously reported events (i.e., those collected as free-text verbatim terms)

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEBODSYS
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Dictionary derived. Body system or organ class used by the sponsor from the coding dictionary (e.g., MedDRA). When using a multi-axial dictionary such as MedDRA, this should contain the SOC used for the sponsor's analyses and summary tables which may not necessarily be the primary SOC.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEBDSYCD
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Body System or Organ Class Code
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Dictionary derived. Code for the body system or organ class used by the sponsor. When using a multi-axial dictionary such as MedDRA, this should contain the SOC used for the sponsor's analyses and summary tables, which may not necessarily be the primary SOC.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESOC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Dictionary-derived text description of the primary System Organ Class. Will be the same as AEBODSYS if the primary SOC was used for analysis.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESOCCD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Dictionary-derived code for the primary System Organ Class. Will be the same as AEBDSYCD if the primary SOC was used for analysis.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AELOC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes anatomical location relevant for the event (e.g., LEFT ARM for skin rash).

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESEV
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: The severity or intensity of the event. Examples: MILD, MODERATE, SEVERE.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESER
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Is this a serious event?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEACN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes changes to the study treatment as a result of the event. AEACN is specifically for the relationship to study treatment. AEACNOTH is for actions unrelated to dose adjustments of study treatment. Examples of AEACN values include ICH E2B values: DRUG WITHDRAWN, DOSE REDUCED, DOSE INCREASED, DOSE NOT CHANGED, UNKNOWN or NOT APPLICABLE

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEACNOTH
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes other actions taken as a result of the event that are unrelated to dose adjustments of study treatment. Usually reported as free text. Example: TREATMENT UNBLINDED. PRIMARY CARE PHYSICIAN NOTIFIED.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEREL
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Records the investigator's opinion as to the causality of the event to the treatment. ICH E2A and E2B examples include NOT RELATED, UNLIKELY RELATED, POSSIBLY RELATED, RELATED. Controlled Terminology may be defined in the future. Check with regulatory authority for population of this variable

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AERELNST
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Records the investigator's opinion as to whether the event may have been due to a treatment other than study drug. May be reported as free text. Example: MORE LIKELY RELATED TO ASPIRIN USE..

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEPATT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to indicate the pattern of the event over time. Examples: INTERMITTENT, CONTINUOUS, SINGLE EVENT.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEOUT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Description of the outcome of an event.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESCAN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Was the serious event associated with the development of cancer?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESCONG
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Was the serious event associated with congenital anomaly or birth defect?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESDISAB
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Did the serious event result in persistent or significant disability/incapacity?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESDTH
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Did the serious event result in death?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESHOSP
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Did the serious event require or prolong hospitalization?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESLIFE
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Was the serious event life threatening?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESOD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Did the serious event occur with an overdose?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESMIE
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Do additional categories for seriousness apply?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AECONTRT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Was another treatment given because of the occurrence of the event?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AETOXGR
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Toxicity grade according to a standard toxicity scale such as Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events v3.0 (CTCAE). Sponsor should specify name of the scale and version used in the metadata (see 6.2.1.1, Assumption 6c). If value is from a numeric scale, represent only the number (e.g., 2 and not Grade 2).

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AESTDY
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Study Day of Start of Adverse Event
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Study day of start of adverse event relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEENDY
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Study Day of End of Adverse Event
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Study day of end of event relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEDUR
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Collected duration and unit of an adverse event. Used only if collected on the CRF and not derived from start and end date/times. Example: P1DT2H (for 1 day, 2 hours).

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEENRF
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes the end of the event relative to the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point (RFSTDTC) and a discrete ending point (RFENDTC) of the trial.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEENRTPT
ProSDTMVariable.Description: End Relative to Reference Time Point
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifies the end of the event as being before or after the reference time point defined by variable AEENTPT.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: AEENTPT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Description of date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the reference point referred to by AEENRTPT. Examples: 2003-12-25 or VISIT 2.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CESTRF
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes the start of the clinical event relative to the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point (represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics).

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CEENRF
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes the end of the event relative to the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point (represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics).

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CESTRTPT
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Start Relative to Reference Time Point
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifies the start of the observation as being before or after the reference time point defined by variable CESTTPT.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CESTTPT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the sponsor-defined reference point referred to by --STRTPT. Examples: 2003-12-15 or VISIT 1.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CEENRTPT
ProSDTMVariable.Description: End Relative to Reference Time Point
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifies the end of the event as being before or after the reference time point defined by variable CEENTPT.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: CEENTPT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the reference point referred to by CEENRTPT. Examples: 2003-12-25 or VISIT 2.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: STUDYID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique identifier for a study.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOMAIN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: USUBJID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: SPDEVID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined identifier for the device.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DESEQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of device records within subject records within a domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DESPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined reference number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DETERM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Verbatim name of the observed event.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DEMODIFY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: The modified text for DETERM

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DEDECOD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Dictionary-derived form of the event described in DETERM.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DECAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to define a categorization level for events.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DESCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to define a further category level for events.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DEPRESP
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to indicate whether (Y/null) information about a specific event was solicited on the CRF.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DEOCCUR
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: When information about specific events is solicited, DEOCCUR is used to indicate whether or not (Y/N) a particular pre-specified event occurred.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DESTAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: The status indicates that the pre-specified question was not answered.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DEREASND
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Reason DESTAT was not done

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DESEV
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Severity of Event

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DEACNDEV
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes Action Taken with respect to the device

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISITNUM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Clinical encounter number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISIT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISITDY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Planned study day of the visit based upon RFSTDTC in Demographics.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DEDTC
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Date of Device Event Data Collection
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Date the device event information was collected.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DESTDTC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Start date/time of the device event.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DEENDTC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: End date/time of the device event.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DEDY
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Study Day of Device Event Data Collection
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Study day of Device Event observation, measured as integer days.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DESTDY
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Study Day of Device Event Start Date/Time
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Study day of start of Device Event, measured as integer days.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DEENDY
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Study Day of Device Event End Date/Time
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Study day of end of Device Event, measured as integer days.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: STUDYID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique identifier for a study.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOMAIN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: SPDEVID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined identifier for the device.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DTSEQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of device records within subject records (if applicable) within a domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DTTERM
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Reported Term for the Tracking Event
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Verbatim or preprinted term for the activity that occurs.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DTMODIFY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Modified term entered to allow mapping of verbatim term to dictionary term

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DTDECOD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Dictionary-derived text description of DTTERM or DTMODIFY.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DTPARTY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Person or organization accountable for the device at the conclusion of the action specified in DTTERM.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DTPRTYID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: An identifier for the responsible group/role (e.g. site, subject).

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DTCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Define a categorization level for a group of related records.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DTSCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Defines a further categorization level for a group of related conditions or events.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DTDTC
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Date/Time of Device Tracking Event Collection
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Date/Time of the tracking event information was collected.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DTSTDTC
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Start Date/Time of Device Tracking Event
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Start date/time of tracking event.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: STUDYID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique identifier for a study within the submission.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOMAIN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: USUBJID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique subject identifier within the submission.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DASEQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DAGRPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a subject.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DAREFID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Internal or external identifier such as label number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DASPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined reference number. Perhaps pre-printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor's operational database. Examples: Line number on the Drug Accountability page, drug label code.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DATESTCD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Short character value for DATEST used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical format to a horizontal format. The short value can be up to 8 characters and cannot begin with a number or contain characters other than letters, numbers or underscores. Example: DISPAMT, RETAMT.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DATEST
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Verbatim name, corresponding to the topic variable, of the test or examination used to obtain the drug accountability assessment. The value in DATEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Example: Dispensed Amount, Returned Amount.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DACAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to define a category of related records. Examples: STUDY MEDICATION, RESCUE MEDICATION.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DASCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to define a further categorization level for a group of related records.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DAORRES
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Result of the Drug Accountability assessment as originally received or collected.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DAORRESU
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unit for DAORRES.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DASTRESC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Contains the result value for all Drug Accountability assessments, copied or derived from DAORRES in a standard format or in standard units. DASTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in DASTRESN.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DASTRESN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from DASTRESC. DASTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DASTRESU
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Standardized units used for DASTRESC and DASTRESN.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DASTAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to indicate that a drug accountability assessment was not done. Should be null or have a value of NOT DONE.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DAREASND
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Reason not done. Used in conjunction with DASTAT when value is NOT DONE.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISITNUM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Clinical encounter number. 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISIT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISITDY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Planned study day of the visit based upon RFSTDTC in Demographics.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DADY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Study day of drug accountability assessment, measured as integer days. 2. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: STUDYID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique identifier for a study.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOMAIN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: USUBJID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DDSEQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sequence number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DDTESTCD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Short name of the measurement, test, or examination described in DDTEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in DDTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g., 1TEST is not valid). DDTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples: DIAGPRIM, DIAGSEC, DTHWIT

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DDTEST
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Long name for DDTESTCD. The value in DDTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: Primary Diagnosis, Secondary Diagnosis, Was Death Witnessed?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DDORRES
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Result of the test defined in DDTEST, as originally received or collected.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DDSTRESC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Contains the result or finding copied or derived from DDORRES in a standard format.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DDRESCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to categorize the result of a finding. Examples: TREATMENT RELATED, NONTREATMENT RELATED, UNDETERMINED, ACCIDENTAL

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DDEVAL
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Role of the person who provided the evaluation.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DDDTC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Date/time of collection of the diagnosis or other death assessment data in ISO 8601 format. This is not necessarily the date of death.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DDDY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Study day of the collection, in integer days. The algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in the Demographics (DM) domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: STUDYID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique identifier for a study.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOMAIN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: USUBJID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGSEQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGGRPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a subject.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGREFID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Internal or external ECG identifier. Example: UUID.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGSPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined reference number. Perhaps pre-printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor's operational database. Example: Line number from the ECG page.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGTESTCD
ProSDTMVariable.Description: ECG Test or Examination Short Name
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Short name of the measurement, test, or examination described in EGTEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in EGTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g., 1TEST). EGTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples :PRMEAN, QTMEAN

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGTEST
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Verbatim name of the test or examination used to obtain the measurement or finding. The value in EGTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: Summary (Mean) PR Duration, Summary (Mean) QT Duration

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to categorize ECG observations across subjects. Examples: MEASUREMENT, FINDING, INTERVAL

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGSCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: A further categorization of the ECG.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGPOS
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Position of the subject during a measurement or examination. Examples: SUPINE, STANDING, SITTING.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGORRES
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Result or Finding in Original Units
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Result of the ECG measurement or finding as originally received or collected. Examples of expected values are 62 or 0.151 when the result is an interval or measurement, or ATRIAL FIBRILLATION or QT PROLONGATION when the result is a finding.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGORRESU
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for EGORRES. Examples: sec or msec.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGSTRESC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from EGORRES in a standard format or standard units. EGSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in EGSTRESN. For example, if a test has results of NONE, NEG, and NEGATIVE in EGORRES and these results effectively have the same meaning, they could be represented in standard format in EGSTRESC as NEGATIVE. For other examples, see general assumptions. Additional examples of result data: SINUS BRADYCARDIA, ATRIAL FLUTTER, ATRIAL FIBRILLATION.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGSTRESN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from EGSTRESC. EGSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGSTRESU
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Standardized unit used for EGSTRESC or EGSTRESN.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGSTAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to indicate an ECG was not done, or an ECG measurement was not taken. Should be null if a result exists in EGORRES.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGREASND
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes why a measurement or test was not performed. Examples: BROKEN EQUIPMENT or SUBJECT REFUSED. Used in conjunction with EGSTAT when value is NOT DONE.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGXFN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: File name and path for the external ECG Waveform file.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGNAM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Name or identifier of the laboratory or vendor who provided the test results.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGLOC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: The lead used for the measurement, examples, V1, V6, aVR, I, II, III.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGMETHOD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Method of the ECG test. Examples: 12 LEAD STANDARD.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGBLFL
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Indicator used to identify a baseline value. The value should be Y or null.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGDRVFL
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to indicate a derived record. The value should be Y or null. Records which represent the average of other records, or that do not come from the CRF, or are not as originally collected or received are examples of records that would be derived for the submission datasets. If EGDRVFL=Y, then EGORRES could be null, with EGSTRESC, and (if numeric) EGSTRESN having the derived value.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGEVAL
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Role of the person who provided the evaluation. Used only for results that are subjective (e.g., assigned by a person or a group). Should be null for records that contain collected or derived data. Examples: INVESTIGATOR, ADJUDICATION COMMITTEE, VENDOR.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISITNUM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Clinical encounter number. 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISIT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISITDY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Planned study day of the visit based upon RFSTDTC in Demographics.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGDTC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Date of ECG.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGDY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Study day of the ECG, measured as integer days. 2. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGTPT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Text Description of time when measurement should be taken. 2. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See EGTPTNUM and EGTPTREF. Examples: Start, 5 min post.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGTPTNUM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Numerical version of EGTPT to aid in sorting.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGELTM
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Planned elapsed time (in ISO 8601) relative to a fixed time point reference (EGTPTREF). Not a clock time or a date time variable. Represented as an ISO 8601 duration. Examples: -PT15M to represent the period of 15 minutes prior to the reference point indicated by EGTPTREF, or PT8H to represent the period of 8 hours after the reference point indicated by EGTPTREF.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGTPTREF
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Name of the fixed reference point referred to by EGELTM, EGTPTNUM, and EGTPT. Examples: PREVIOUS DOSE, PREVIOUS MEAL.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EGRFTDTC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Date/time of the reference time point, EGTPTREF.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: STUDYID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique identifier for a study.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOMAIN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: USUBJID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: IESEQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: IESPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined reference number. Perhaps pre-printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor's operational database. Example: Inclusion or Exclusion criteria number from CRF.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: IETESTCD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Short name of the criterion described in IETEST. The value in IETESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g.1TEST). IETESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples: IN01, EX01.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: IETEST
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Verbatim description of the inclusion or exclusion criterion that was the exception for the subject within the study. IETEST cannot be longer than 200 characters.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: IECAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to define a category of related records across subjects.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: IESCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: A further categorization of the exception criterion. Can be used to distinguish criteria for a sub-study or for to categorize as a major or minor exceptions. Examples: MAJOR, MINOR.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: IEORRES
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Original response to Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion question. Inclusion or Exclusion criterion met?

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: IESTRESC
ProSDTMVariable.Description: I/E Criterion Result in Std Format
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Response to Inclusion/Exclusion criterion result in standard format.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISITNUM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Clinical encounter number. 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISIT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISITDY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Planned study day of the visit based upon RFSTDTC in Demographics.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: IEDY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Study day of collection of the inclusion/exclusion exceptions, measured as integer days. 2. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics. This formula should be consistent across the submission.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: STUDYID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique Identifier for a study.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOMAIN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: USUBJID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across a submission.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISSEQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sequence number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISGRPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a subject.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISREFID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Internal or external specimen identifier. Example: 458975-01.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISSPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined identifier.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISTESTCD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Short name of the measurement, test, or examination described in ISTEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in ISTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number. ISTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Sponsor should first check the lab terminology for the LBTEST/LBTESTCD values until CDISC attaches published controlled terminology.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISTEST
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Verbatim name of the test or examination used to obtain the measurement or finding. The value in ISTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. (Example: Immunoglobulin E). Sponsor should first check the lab terminology for the LBTEST/LBTESTCD values until CDISC attaches published controlled terminology.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to define a category of Topic-variable values across subjects. Example: SEROLOGY

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISSCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: A further categorization of ISCAT.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISORRES
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Results or Findings in Original Units
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Results of measurement or finding as originally received or collected.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISORRESU
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for ISORRES. Examples: Index Value, gpELISA, unit/mL.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISSTRESC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from ISORRES, in a standard format or in standard units. ISSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in ISSTRESN.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISSTRESN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from ISSTRESC. ISSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISSTRESU
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Standardized units used for ISSTRESC and ISSTRESN. Examples: Index Value, gpELISA, unit/mL.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISSTAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to indicate a test was not done. Should be null if a result exists in ISORRES.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISREASND
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes why a measurement or test was not performed. Used in conjunction with ISSTAT when value is NOT DONE.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISNAM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Name or identifier of the laboratory or vendor who provided the test results

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISSPEC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Defines the types of specimen used for a measurement. Example: SERUM.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISMETHOD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Method of test or examination. Examples: ELISA, ELISPOT.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISBLFL
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Indicator used to identify a baseline value. Should be Y or null.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISLLOQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Indicates the lower limit of quantitation for an assay. Units will be those used for ISSTRESU.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISITNUM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Clinical encounter number. 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISIT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISITDY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Planned study day of the visit based upon RFSTDTC in Demographics.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISDTC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Collection date and time of an observation represented in ISO 8601.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: ISDY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Actual study day of visit/collection/exam expressed in integer days relative to sponsor- defined RFSTDTC in Demographics.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: STUDYID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique identifier for a study.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOMAIN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: USUBJID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBSEQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBGRPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a subject.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBREFID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Internal or external specimen identifier. Example: Specimen ID.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBSPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined reference number. Perhaps pre-printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor's operational database. Example: Line number on the Lab page.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBTESTCD
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Lab Test or Examination Short Name
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Short name of the measurement, test, or examination described in LBTEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in LBTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g.1TEST). LBTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples: ALT, LDH.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBTEST
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Verbatim name of the test or examination used to obtain the measurement or finding. Note any test normally performed by a clinical laboratory is considered a lab test. The value in LBTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: Alanine Aminotransferase, Lactate Dehydrogenase.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to define a category of related records across subjects. Examples: such as HEMATOLOGY, URINALYSIS, CHEMISTRY.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBSCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: A further categorization of a test category such as DIFFERENTIAL, COAGULATON, LIVER FUNCTION, ELECTROLYTES.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBORRES
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Result or Finding in Original Units
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Result of the measurement or finding as originally received or collected.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBORRESU
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for LBORRES. Example: g/L.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBORNRLO
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Reference Range Lower Limit in Orig Unit
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Lower end of reference range for continuous measurements in original units. Should be populated only for continuous results.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBORNRHI
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Reference Range Upper Limit in Orig Unit
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Upper end of reference range for continuous measurements in original units. Should be populated only for continuous results.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBSTRESC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from LBORRES in a standard format or standard units. LBSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in LBSTRESN. For example, if a test has results NONE, NEG, and NEGATIVE in LBORRES and these results effectively have the same meaning, they could be represented in standard format in LBSTRESC as NEGATIVE. For other examples, see general assumptions.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBSTRESN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from LBSTRESC. LBSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBSTRESU
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Standardized unit used for LBSTRESC or LBSTRESN.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBSTNRLO
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Lower end of reference range for continuous measurements for LBSTRESC/LBSTRESN in standardized units. Should be populated only for continuous results.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBSTNRHI
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Upper end of reference range for continuous measurements in standardized units. Should be populated only for continuous results.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBSTNRC
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Reference Range for Char Rslt-Std Units
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: For normal range values that are character in ordinal scale or if categorical ranges were supplied (e.g., -1 to +1, NEGATIVE TO TRACE).

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBNRIND
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Indicates where the value falls with respect to reference range defined by LBORNRLO and LBORNRHI, LBSTNRLO and LBSTNRHI, or by LBSTNRC. Examples: NORMAL, ABNORMAL, HIGH, LOW. 2. Sponsors should specify in the study metadata (Comments column in the define.xml) whether LBNRIND refers to the original or standard reference ranges and results. 3. Should not be used to indicate clinical significance.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBSTAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to indicate exam not done. Should be null if a result exists in LBORRES.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBREASND
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes why a measurement or test was not performed such as BROKEN EQUIPMENT, SUBJECT REFUSED, or SPECIMEN LOST. Used in conjunction with LBSTAT when value is NOT DONE.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBNAM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: The name or identifier of the laboratory that performed the test.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBLOINC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Dictionary-derived LOINC Code for LBTEST. 2. The sponsor is expected to provide the dictionary name and version used to map the terms utilizing the define.xml external codelist attributes

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBSPEC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Defines the type of specimen used for a measurement. Examples: SERUM, PLASMA, URINE.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: LBSPCCND
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Free or standardized text describing the condition of the specimen e.g. HEMOLYZED, ICTERIC, LIPEMIC etc.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: STUDYID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique identifier for a study.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOMAIN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: SPDEVID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined identifier for the device.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOSEQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of device records within subject records within a DOMAIN

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOGRPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a device.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOREFID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Internal or external identifier.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOSPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined reference number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOTESTCD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Short name of the measurement, test, or examination described in DOTEST.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOTEST
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Verbatim name of the test or examination used to obtain the measurement or finding.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Defines a Category of related records.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOSCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: A further Categorization of a measurement or examination

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOORRES
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Result or Finding in Original Units
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Result of the Device Property as originally observed or collected.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOORRESU
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Original units in which the data were collected.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: TREVALID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: The Evaluator Specified variable is used in conjunction with TREVAL to provide an additional level of detail. When multiple assessors play the role identified in TREVAL, values of TREVALID will attribute a row of data to a particular assessor. TREVALID should not contain the names of the assessors, or a code identifier for a specific assessor, but should contain values such as RADIOLOGIST, RADIOLOGIST 1 or RADIOLOGIST 2. The TREVALID variable is subject to CDISC Controlled Terminology. Note TREVAL must also be populated when TREVALID is populated. See Assumption 7.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: TRACPTFL
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: In cases where more than one independent assessor (e.g. RADIOLOGIST 1, RADIOLOGIST 2, ADJUDICATOR) provide independent assessments at the same timepoint this flag identifies the record that is considered to be the accepted assessment.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISITNUM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Clinical encounter number. 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISIT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: EPOCH
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Epoch associated with the Element in the planned sequence of Elements for the ARM to which the subject was assigned

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: TRDTC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: TRDTC variable represents the date of the scan/image/physical exam not the date that the image was read to identify tumors. TRDTC variable does not represent the VISIT date.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: TRDY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Study day of the scan/image/physical exam, measured as integer days. 2. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: STUDYID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique identifier for a study.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOMAIN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: USUBJID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSSEQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSGRPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain to support relationships within the domain and between domains. In MS, used to link to organism in MB.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSREFID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Internal or external specimen identifier. Example: Specimen ID.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSSPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined reference number. Perhaps pre-printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor's operational database.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSTESTCD
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Short name of the measurement, test, or finding described in MSTEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in MSTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g."1TEST). MSTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples for GROWTH findings: EXTGROW, COLCOUNT. For SUSCEPTIBILITY findings, the test is the drug the organism was tested with, i.e. PENICLLN, AMOXCLLN.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSTEST
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Verbatim name of the test or examination used to obtain the measurement or finding. Examples for GROWTH findings: Extent of Growth, Colony Count. Examples for SUSCEPTIBILITY findings: Amoxicillin Susceptibility, Penicillin Susceptibility

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to define a Category of related records. Examples: GROWTH, SUSCEPTIBILITY.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSSCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: A further Categorization of a test Category. Examples: CULTURE, ISOLATE

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSORRES
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Result or Finding in Original Units
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Result of the Microbiology Organism measurement or finding as originally received or collected. Examples for GROWTH findings: GROWTH INTO 3RD QUADRANT. Examples for SUSCEPTIBLITY findings:.0080,.0023

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSORRESU
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for MSORRES. Example: mcg/mL

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSSTRESC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from MSORRES in a standard format or standard units. MSSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in MSSTRESN. For example, if a test has results "+3 MODERATE", "MOD", and "MODERATE", and in MSORRES and these results effectively have the same meaning, they could be represented in standard format in MSSTRESC as "MODERATE".

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSSTRESN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from MSSTRESC. MSSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSSTRESU
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Standardized unit used for MSSTRESC and MSSTRESN.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSRESCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to categorize the result of a finding in a standard format. Example for SUSCEPTIBILITY finding: SUSCEPTIBLE, INTERMEDIATE, RESISTANT, or UNKNOWN.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSSTAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to indicate a test on an organism was not done, or a test was not performed. Should be null if a result exists in MSORRES or have a value of NOT DONE.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSREASND
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Reason not done. Describes why a measurement or test was not performed. Used in conjunction with MSSTAT when value is NOT DONE. Example: SAMPLE LOST

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSNAM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Name or identifier of the laboratory or vendor that provided the test results.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSLOINC
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Dictionary-derived LOINC Code for MSTEST. 2. The sponsor is expected to provide the dictionary name and version used to map the terms utilizing the define.xml external codelist attributes

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSMETHOD
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Method of the test or examination. Example for SUSCEPTIBILITY: ETEST, BROTH DILUTION.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSBLFL
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Indicator used to identify a baseline value. The value should be "Y" or null.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSDRVFL
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to indicate a derived record. The value should be Y or null. Records that represent the average of other records or some other derivation, and those that do not come from the CRF, are examples of records that would be derived for the submission datasets. If MSDRVFL=Y, then MSORRES may be null, with MSSTRESC and (if numeric) MSSTRESN having the derived value.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISITNUM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Clinical encounter number. 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISIT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. 1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISITDY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Planned study day of the visit based upon RFSTDTC in Demographics.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSDY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Study day of the test, measured as integer days. 2. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics. This formula should be consistent across the submission.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSTPT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Text Description of time when test should be done. 2. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See MSTPTNUM and MSTPTREF. Examples: Start, 5 min post.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSTPTNUM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Numerical version of MSTPT to aid in sorting.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSELTM
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Elapsed time (in ISO 8601) relative to a planned fixed reference (MSTPTREF). This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time or a date time variable. Examples: "-PT15M" to represent the period of 15 minutes prior to the reference point indicated by MSTPTREF, or "P8H" to represent the period of 8 hours after the reference point indicated by MSTPTREF.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: MSTPTREF
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Name of the fixed reference point referred to by MSELTM, MSTPTNUM, and MSTPT. Example: PREVIOUS DOSE.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: STUDYID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique identifier for a study.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOMAIN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: USUBJID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique subject identifier within the submission.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCSEQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCGRPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain to support relationships within the domain and between domains.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCREFID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Internal or external specimen identifier. Example: Specimen ID.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCSPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined reference number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCTESTCD
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Short name of the analyte or specimen characteristic. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in PCTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g., "1TEST"). PCTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples: ASA, VOL, SPG.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCTEST
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Name of the analyte or specimen characteristic. Note any test normally performed by a clinical laboratory is considered a lab test. The value in PCTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: Acetylsalicylic Acid, Volume, Specific Gravity.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to define a Category of related records. Examples: ANALYTE, SPECIMEN PROPERTY.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCSCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: A further Categorization of a test Category.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCORRES
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Result or Finding in Original Units
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Result of the measurement or finding as originally received or collected.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCORRESU
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for PCORRES. Example: mg/L.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCSTRESC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from PCORRES in a standard format or standard units. PCSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in PCSTRESN. For example, if a test has results "NONE", "NEG", and "NEGATIVE" in PCORRES and these results effectively have the same meaning, they could be represented in standard format in PCSTRESC as "NEGATIVE". For other examples, see general assumptions.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCSTRESN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from PCSTRESC. PCSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCSTRESU
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Standardized unit used for PCSTRESC and PCSTRESN.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCSTAT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to indicate a result was not obtained. Should be null if a result exists in PCORRES.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCREASND
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Describes why a result was not obtained such as SPECIMEN LOST. Used in conjunction with PCSTAT when value is NOT DONE.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCNAM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Name or identifier of the laboratory or vendor who provides the test results.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCSPEC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Defines the type of specimen used for a measurement. Examples: SERUM, PLASMA, URINE.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCSPCCND
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Free or standardized text describing the condition of the specimen e.g. HEMOLYZED, ICTERIC, LIPEMIC etc.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCMETHOD
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Method of the test or examination. Examples include HPLC/MS, ELISA. This should contain sufficient information and granularity to allow differentiation of various methods that might have been used within a study.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCFAST
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Indicator used to identify fasting status.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCDRVFL
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to indicate a derived record. The value should be Y or null. Records that represent the average of other records, which do not come from the CRF, are examples of records that would be derived for the submission datasets. If PCDRVFL=Y, then PCORRES should be null with PCSTRESC, and (if numeric) PCSTRESN having the derived value.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCLLOQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Indicates the lower limit of quantitation for an assay. Units should be those used in PCSTRESU.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISITNUM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Clinical encounter number. 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISIT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: VISITDY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Planned study day of the visit based upon RFSTDTC in Demographics.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCDTC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Date/time of specimen collection represented in ISO 8601 character format. If there is no end time, then this will be the collection time.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCENDTC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: End date/time of specimen collection represented in ISO 8601 character format. If there is no end time, the collection time should be stored in PCDTC, and PCENDTC should be null.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCDY
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Actual Study Day of Specimen Collection
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Study day of specimen collection, measured as integer days. 2. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCTPT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: 1. Text Description of time when specimen should be taken. 2. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See PCTPTNUM and PCTPTREF. Examples: Start, 5 min post.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCTPTNUM
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Numerical version of PCTPT to aid in sorting.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCELTM
ProSDTMVariable.Description: Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Planned elapsed time (in ISO 8601) relative to a planned fixed reference (PCTPTREF) such as "PREVIOUS DOSE" or "PREVIOUS MEAL". This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time or a date time variable.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCTPTREF
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Name of the fixed reference point used as a basis for PCTPT, PCTPTNUM, and PCELTM. Example: Most Recent Dose.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCRFTDTC
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Date/time of the reference time point described by PCTPTREF.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PCEVLINT
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Evaluation Interval associated with a PCTEST record represented in ISO 8601 character format. Example: "-P2H" to represent an interval of 2 hours prior to a PCTPT.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: STUDYID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Unique identifier for a study.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: DOMAIN
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: USUBJID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PESEQ
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PEGRPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a subject.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PESPID
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Sponsor-defined reference number. Perhaps pre-printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor‘s operational database. Example: Line number on a CRF.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PETESTCD
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Short name of the measurement, test, or examination described in PETEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in PETESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g."1TEST"). PETESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PETEST
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Verbatim term part of the body examined. The value in PETEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: Cardiovascular and Respiratory. For subject-level exam, value should be "Physical examination".

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PEMODIFY
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: If PEORRES is modified as part of a defined procedure, then PEMODIFY will contain the modified text.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PECAT
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Used to define a Category of examination. Examples: GENERAL, NEUROLOGICAL.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PESCAT
ProSDTMVariable.Format: Variable may be subject to controlled terminology.
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: A further Categorization of the examination. Used if needed to add further detail to PECAT.

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PEBODSYS
ProSDTMVariable.Notes: Body system or organ class ( MedDRA SOC) that is involved in a measurement from the standard hierarchy (e.g., MedDRA).

ProSDTMVariable.Caption: PEORRES
